# ============================================================
# INVENTORY CORE POLICY
# ============================================================

status: canonical
layer: policy
domain: inventory
scope: inventory.core
system: civilization-os
owner: Boss
prepared_by: Zero

## purpose
Defines policy constraints for inventory.

## policy_rules
Inventory policy constrains:
- who may view stock and movement detail
- who may reserve/move/deplete inventory
- what inventory detail may be disclosed
- when inventory paths must be denied or escalated

## required_behavior
- stock-control scope must be explicit
- movement/depletion scope must be explicit
- disclosure scope must be explicit
- denial behavior must be explicit

## disclosure_matrix
- public stock summary
- holder/operator detail
- reviewer detail
- historical inventory detail
- denied output

## allowed_denied_matrix
- allow reservation/movement/depletion only for valid scope
- allow disclosure only for allowed actors
- deny hidden stock manipulation
- deny disclosure beyond allowed scope

## escalation_rules
If inventory context,
movement basis,
depletion scope,
or disclosure scope is unclear,
the inventory path must stop and escalate.

## review_checklist
- stock-control policy is explicit
- movement/depletion policy is explicit
- disclosure matrix exists
- denial behavior is explicit
